Boil your kettle and pre-heat your #oven to 190 degrees. Remove the top and 
bottom of the @courgette{4} and slice in half lengthways, then cut each half 
lengthways into four slices. Chop your courgette into roughly 2cm cubes. 
Roughly chop the @coriander{1}.

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}. Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a large 
#non-stick pan{} on medium heat and fry your ginger for ~{2%mins}.

Add the @basmati rice{350%g} to your ginger in the #pan and a pinch of @salt{}. 
Stir together and add the @water{700%ml}. Put a lid on the pan and cook on low 
heat for ~{10%mins}. Leave off the heat for ~{10%mins} and don't peek under the 
lid until 20 mins are up.

Place another pan on medium heat without oil and add in the @coriander seeds{1} 
and @chilli flakes{1/4%tsp}.

> Use less chilli if you don't like your food too spicy!

Cook for ~{2%mins} and then thoroughly grind with a #pestle and mortar{}. 

> You can use the back of a spoon on your chopping board too.

Mix the @greek style yoghurt{2} with all but a pinch of your toasted coriander 
seed and chilli flake powder. Mix in half your fresh coriander, the 
@honey{2%tbsp}, a splash of olive oil and a squeeze of the @lime{1} juice. Add 
a pinch of lime zest then season with a little @salt{pinch} and a few grinds of 
@black pepper{a few grinds}.

Coat the @British chicken breasts{4} in your yoghurt mix. Cook on a 
#baking tray{} on the top shelf of your #oven for ~{15%mins}. After 15 mins, 
turn your grill to high and grill your chicken for ~{5%mins} to brown the top. 

> You'll know the chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} on high heat in the pan you used for your seeds 
and flakes. Stir-fry your courgette for ~{4%mins}. Season with a pinch of 
@salt{} and some @pepper{} and the remaining toasted coriander seeds and fresh 
coriander.

To serve, simply fluff up your rice using a #fork{}. Top it with your chicken 
and a side portion of your stir-fried courgette. Squeeze over a splash of lime 
juice.